http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Woman%E2%80%99s-body-found-in-bag/article14594867.ece

The Byadarahalli police recovered the highly decomposed body of an unidentified woman in a travel bag near a private college on the outskirts of the city on Sunday.Some passers-by noticed a foul smell from the bag with flies hovering around it and alerted the police.The deceased was aged around 25 to 30 years and was murdered a few days ago as the body was highly decomposed, a senior police officer said. The body has been shifted to the Ramanagaram government hospital and the police have alerted the stations in and around the State to cross-check with missing cases filed. — Special Correspondent